40void
41gk104_fifo_uevent_fini(struct nvkm_fifo *fifo)
42{
43 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->engine.subdev.device;
44 nvkm_mask(device, 0x002140, 0x80000000, 0x00000000);
45}
46
47void
48gk104_fifo_uevent_init(struct nvkm_fifo *fifo)
49{
50 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->engine.subdev.device;
51 nvkm_mask(device, 0x002140, 0x80000000, 0x80000000);
52}

54void
55gk104_fifo_runlist_update(struct gk104_fifo *fifo, u32 engine)
56{
57 struct gk104_fifo_engn *engn = &fifo->engine[engine];
58 struct gk104_fifo_chan *chan;
59 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
60 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
61 struct nvkm_memory *cur;
62 int nr = 0;
63
64 mutex_lock(&subdev->mutex);
65 cur = engn->runlist[engn->cur_runlist];
66 engn->cur_runlist = !engn->cur_runlist;
67
68 nvkm_kmap(cur);
69 list_for_each_entry(chan, &engn->chan, head) {
70 nvkm_wo32(cur, (nr * 8) + 0, chan->base.chid);
71 nvkm_wo32(cur, (nr * 8) + 4, 0x00000000);
72 nr++;
73 }
74 nvkm_done(cur);
75
76 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002270, nvkm_memory_addr(cur) >> 12);
77 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002274, (engine << 20) | nr);
78
79#ifdef __NetBSD__
80 /* XXX it is wrong to wait under mutex */
81 if (cold) {
82 uint count = 2000;
83 while (count-- > 0) {
84 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002284 +
85 (engine * 0x08)) & 0x00100000))
86 break;
87 delay(1000);
88 }
89 if (count == 0)
90 nvkm_error(subdev, "runlist %d update timeout\n",
91 engine);
92 } else {
93 int ret;
94
95 spin_lock(&engn->lock);
96 DRM_SPIN_TIMED_WAIT_NOINTR_UNTIL(ret, &engn->wait, &engn->lock,
97 msecs_to_jiffies(2000),
98 !(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002284 +
99 (engine * 0x08)) & 0x00100000));
100 if (ret == 0)
101 nvkm_error(subdev, "runlist %d update timeout\n",
102 engine);
103 spin_unlock(&engn->lock);
104 }
105#else
106 if (wait_event_timeout(engn->wait, !(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002284 +
107 (engine * 0x08)) & 0x00100000),
108 msecs_to_jiffies(2000)) == 0)
109 nvkm_error(subdev, "runlist %d update timeout\n", engine);
110#endif
111 mutex_unlock(&subdev->mutex);
112}

114static inline struct nvkm_engine *
115gk104_fifo_engine(struct gk104_fifo *fifo, u32 engn)
116{
117 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
118 u64 subdevs = gk104_fifo_engine_subdev(engn);
119 if (subdevs)
120 return nvkm_device_engine(device, __ffs(subdevs));
121 return NULL;
122}
123
124static void
125gk104_fifo_recover_work(struct work_struct *work)
126{
127 struct gk104_fifo *fifo = container_of(work, typeof(*fifo), fault);
128 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
129 struct nvkm_engine *engine;
130 unsigned long flags;
131 u32 engn, engm = 0;
132 u64 mask, todo;
133
134 spin_lock_irqsave(&fifo->base.lock, flags);
135 mask = fifo->mask;
136 fifo->mask = 0ULL;
137 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&fifo->base.lock, flags);
138
139 for (todo = mask;
140 todo && (engn = __ffs64(todo), 1);
141 todo &= ~(1 << engn))
142 engm |= 1 << gk104_fifo_subdev_engine(engn);
143 nvkm_mask(device, 0x002630, engm, engm);
144
145 for (todo = mask;
146 todo && (engn = __ffs64(todo), 1);
147 todo &= ~(1 << engn)) {
148 if ((engine = nvkm_device_engine(device, engn))) {
149 nvkm_subdev_fini(&engine->subdev, false);
150 WARN_ON(nvkm_subdev_init(&engine->subdev));
151 }
152 gk104_fifo_runlist_update(fifo, gk104_fifo_subdev_engine(engn));
153 }
154
155 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x00262c, engm);
156 nvkm_mask(device, 0x002630, engm, 0x00000000);
157}
158
159static void
160gk104_fifo_recover(struct gk104_fifo *fifo, struct nvkm_engine *engine,
161 struct gk104_fifo_chan *chan)
162{
163 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
164 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
165 u32 chid = chan->base.chid;
166
167 nvkm_error(subdev, "%s engine fault on channel %d, recovering...\n",
168 nvkm_subdev_name[engine->subdev.index], chid);
169 assert_spin_locked(&fifo->base.lock);
170
171 nvkm_mask(device, 0x800004 + (chid * 0x08), 0x00000800, 0x00000800);
172 list_del_init(&chan->head);
173 chan->killed = true;
174
175 fifo->mask |= 1ULL << engine->subdev.index;
176 schedule_work(&fifo->fault);
177}

190static void
191gk104_fifo_intr_bind(struct gk104_fifo *fifo)
192{
193 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
194 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
195 u32 intr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00252c);
196 u32 code = intr & 0x000000ff;
197 const struct nvkm_enum *en =
198 nvkm_enum_find(gk104_fifo_bind_reason, code);
199
200 nvkm_error(subdev, "BIND_ERROR %02x [%s]\n", code, en ? en->name : "");
201}

203static const struct nvkm_enum
204gk104_fifo_sched_reason[] = {
205 { 0x0a, "CTXSW_TIMEOUT" },
206 {}
207};
208
209static void
210gk104_fifo_intr_sched_ctxsw(struct gk104_fifo *fifo)
211{
212 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
213 struct nvkm_engine *engine;
214 struct gk104_fifo_chan *chan;
215 unsigned long flags;
216 u32 engn;
217
218 spin_lock_irqsave(&fifo->base.lock, flags);
219 for (engn = 0; engn < ARRAY_SIZE(fifo->engine); engn++) {
220 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002640 + (engn * 0x04));
221 u32 busy = (stat & 0x80000000);
222 u32 next = (stat & 0x07ff0000) >> 16;
223 u32 chsw = (stat & 0x00008000);
224 u32 save = (stat & 0x00004000);
225 u32 load = (stat & 0x00002000);
226 u32 prev = (stat & 0x000007ff);
227 u32 chid = load ? next : prev;
228 (void)save;
229
230 if (busy && chsw) {
231 list_for_each_entry(chan, &fifo->engine[engn].chan, head) {
232 if (chan->base.chid == chid) {
233 engine = gk104_fifo_engine(fifo, engn);
234 if (!engine)
235 break;
236 gk104_fifo_recover(fifo, engine, chan);
237 break;
238 }
239 }
240 }
241 }
242 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&fifo->base.lock, flags);
243}
244
245static void
246gk104_fifo_intr_sched(struct gk104_fifo *fifo)
247{
248 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
249 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
250 u32 intr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00254c);
251 u32 code = intr & 0x000000ff;
252 const struct nvkm_enum *en =
253 nvkm_enum_find(gk104_fifo_sched_reason, code);
254
255 nvkm_error(subdev, "SCHED_ERROR %02x [%s]\n", code, en ? en->name : "");
256
257 switch (code) {
258 case 0x0a:
259 gk104_fifo_intr_sched_ctxsw(fifo);
260 break;
261 default:
262 break;
263 }
264}

266static void
267gk104_fifo_intr_chsw(struct gk104_fifo *fifo)
268{
269 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
270 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
271 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00256c);
272 nvkm_error(subdev, "CHSW_ERROR %08x\n", stat);
273 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x00256c, stat);
274}

390static void
391gk104_fifo_intr_fault(struct gk104_fifo *fifo, int unit)
392{
393 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
394 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
395 u32 inst = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002800 + (unit * 0x10));
396 u32 valo = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002804 + (unit * 0x10));
397 u32 vahi = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002808 + (unit * 0x10));
398 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00280c + (unit * 0x10));
399 u32 gpc = (stat & 0x1f000000) >> 24;
400 u32 client = (stat & 0x00001f00) >> 8;
401 u32 write = (stat & 0x00000080);
402 u32 hub = (stat & 0x00000040);
403 u32 reason = (stat & 0x0000000f);
404 const struct nvkm_enum *er, *eu, *ec;
405 struct nvkm_engine *engine = NULL;
406 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan;
407 unsigned long flags;
408 char gpcid[8] = "";
409
410 er = nvkm_enum_find(gk104_fifo_fault_reason, reason);
411 eu = nvkm_enum_find(gk104_fifo_fault_engine, unit);
412 if (hub) {
413 ec = nvkm_enum_find(gk104_fifo_fault_hubclient, client);
414 } else {
415 ec = nvkm_enum_find(gk104_fifo_fault_gpcclient, client);
416 snprintf(gpcid, sizeof(gpcid), "GPC%d/", gpc);
417 }
418
419 if (eu) {
420 switch (eu->data2) {
421 case NVKM_SUBDEV_BAR:
422 nvkm_mask(device, 0x001704, 0x00000000, 0x00000000);
423 break;
424 case NVKM_SUBDEV_INSTMEM:
425 nvkm_mask(device, 0x001714, 0x00000000, 0x00000000);
426 break;
427 case NVKM_ENGINE_IFB:
428 nvkm_mask(device, 0x001718, 0x00000000, 0x00000000);
429 break;
430 default:
431 engine = nvkm_device_engine(device, eu->data2);
432 break;
433 }
434 }
435
436 chan = nvkm_fifo_chan_inst(&fifo->base, (u64)inst << 12, &flags);
437
438 nvkm_error(subdev,
439 "%s fault at %010"PRIx64" engine %02x [%s] client %02x [%s%s] "
440 "reason %02x [%s] on channel %d [%010"PRIx64" %s]\n",
441 write ? "write" : "read", (u64)vahi << 32 | valo,
442 unit, eu ? eu->name : "", client, gpcid, ec ? ec->name : "",
443 reason, er ? er->name : "", chan ? chan->chid : -1,
444 (u64)inst << 12,
445 chan ? chan->object.client->name : "unknown");
446
447 if (engine && chan)
448 gk104_fifo_recover(fifo, engine, (void *)chan);
449 nvkm_fifo_chan_put(&fifo->base, flags, &chan);
450}

486static void
487gk104_fifo_intr_pbdma_0(struct gk104_fifo *fifo, int unit)
488{
489 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
490 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
491 u32 mask = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x04010c + (unit * 0x2000));
492 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x040108 + (unit * 0x2000)) & mask;
493 u32 addr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x0400c0 + (unit * 0x2000));
494 u32 data = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x0400c4 + (unit * 0x2000));
495 u32 chid = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x040120 + (unit * 0x2000)) & 0xfff;
496 u32 subc = (addr & 0x00070000) >> 16;
497 u32 mthd = (addr & 0x00003ffc);
498 u32 show = stat;
499 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan;
500 unsigned long flags;
501 char msg[128];
502
503 if (stat & 0x00800000) {
504 if (device->sw) {
505 if (nvkm_sw_mthd(device->sw, chid, subc, mthd, data))
506 show &= ~0x00800000;
507 }
508 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x0400c0 + (unit * 0x2000), 0x80600008);
509 }
510
511 if (show) {
512 nvkm_snprintbf(msg, sizeof(msg), gk104_fifo_pbdma_intr_0, show);
513 chan = nvkm_fifo_chan_chid(&fifo->base, chid, &flags);
514 nvkm_error(subdev, "PBDMA%d: %08x [%s] ch %d [%010"PRIx64" %s] "
515 "subc %d mthd %04x data %08x\n",
516 unit, show, msg, chid, chan ? chan->inst->addr : 0,
517 chan ? chan->object.client->name : "unknown",
518 subc, mthd, data);
519 nvkm_fifo_chan_put(&fifo->base, flags, &chan);
520 }
521
522 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x040108 + (unit * 0x2000), stat);
523}

534static void
535gk104_fifo_intr_pbdma_1(struct gk104_fifo *fifo, int unit)
536{
537 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
538 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
539 u32 mask = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x04014c + (unit * 0x2000));
540 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x040148 + (unit * 0x2000)) & mask;
541 u32 chid = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x040120 + (unit * 0x2000)) & 0xfff;
542 char msg[128];
543
544 if (stat) {
545 nvkm_snprintbf(msg, sizeof(msg), gk104_fifo_pbdma_intr_1, stat);
546 nvkm_error(subdev, "PBDMA%d: %08x [%s] ch %d %08x %08x\n",
547 unit, stat, msg, chid,
548 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x040150 + (unit * 0x2000)),
549 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x040154 + (unit * 0x2000)));
550 }
551
552 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x040148 + (unit * 0x2000), stat);
553}
554
555static void
556gk104_fifo_intr_runlist(struct gk104_fifo *fifo)
557{
558 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
559 u32 mask = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002a00);
560 while (mask) {
561 u32 engn = __ffs(mask);
562#ifdef __NetBSD__
563 spin_lock(&fifo->engine[engn].lock);
564 DRM_SPIN_WAKEUP_ONE(&fifo->engine[engn].wait,
565 &fifo->engine[engn].lock);
566 spin_unlock(&fifo->engine[engn].lock);
567#else
568 wake_up(&fifo->engine[engn].wait);
569#endif
570 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002a00, 1 << engn);
571 mask &= ~(1 << engn);
572 }
573}
574
575static void
576gk104_fifo_intr_engine(struct gk104_fifo *fifo)
577{
578 nvkm_fifo_uevent(&fifo->base);
579}
580
581void
582gk104_fifo_intr(struct nvkm_fifo *base)
583{
584 struct gk104_fifo *fifo = gk104_fifo(base);
585 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
586 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
587 u32 mask = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002140);
588 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002100) & mask;
589
590 if (stat & 0x00000001) {
591 gk104_fifo_intr_bind(fifo);
592 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002100, 0x00000001);
593 stat &= ~0x00000001;
594 }
595
596 if (stat & 0x00000010) {
597 nvkm_error(subdev, "PIO_ERROR\n");
598 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002100, 0x00000010);
599 stat &= ~0x00000010;
600 }
601
602 if (stat & 0x00000100) {
603 gk104_fifo_intr_sched(fifo);
604 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002100, 0x00000100);
605 stat &= ~0x00000100;
606 }
607
608 if (stat & 0x00010000) {
609 gk104_fifo_intr_chsw(fifo);
610 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002100, 0x00010000);
611 stat &= ~0x00010000;
612 }
613
614 if (stat & 0x00800000) {
615 nvkm_error(subdev, "FB_FLUSH_TIMEOUT\n");
616 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002100, 0x00800000);
617 stat &= ~0x00800000;
618 }
619
620 if (stat & 0x01000000) {
621 nvkm_error(subdev, "LB_ERROR\n");
622 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002100, 0x01000000);
623 stat &= ~0x01000000;
624 }
625
626 if (stat & 0x08000000) {
627 gk104_fifo_intr_dropped_fault(fifo);
628 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002100, 0x08000000);
629 stat &= ~0x08000000;
630 }
631
632 if (stat & 0x10000000) {
633 u32 mask = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00259c);
634 while (mask) {
635 u32 unit = __ffs(mask);
636 gk104_fifo_intr_fault(fifo, unit);
637 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x00259c, (1 << unit));
638 mask &= ~(1 << unit);
639 }
640 stat &= ~0x10000000;
641 }
642
643 if (stat & 0x20000000) {
644 u32 mask = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x0025a0);
645 while (mask) {
646 u32 unit = __ffs(mask);
647 gk104_fifo_intr_pbdma_0(fifo, unit);
648 gk104_fifo_intr_pbdma_1(fifo, unit);
649 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x0025a0, (1 << unit));
650 mask &= ~(1 << unit);
651 }
652 stat &= ~0x20000000;
653 }
654
655 if (stat & 0x40000000) {
656 gk104_fifo_intr_runlist(fifo);
657 stat &= ~0x40000000;
658 }
659
660 if (stat & 0x80000000) {
661 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002100, 0x80000000);
662 gk104_fifo_intr_engine(fifo);
663 stat &= ~0x80000000;
664 }
665
666 if (stat) {
667 nvkm_error(subdev, "INTR %08x\n", stat);
668 nvkm_mask(device, 0x002140, stat, 0x00000000);
669 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002100, stat);
670 }
671}
672
673void
674gk104_fifo_fini(struct nvkm_fifo *base)
675{
676 struct gk104_fifo *fifo = gk104_fifo(base);
677 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
678 flush_work(&fifo->fault);
679 /* allow mmu fault interrupts, even when we're not using fifo */
680 nvkm_mask(device, 0x002140, 0x10000000, 0x10000000);
681}
682
683int
684gk104_fifo_oneinit(struct nvkm_fifo *base)
685{
686 struct gk104_fifo *fifo = gk104_fifo(base);
687 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
688 int ret, i;
689
690 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(fifo->engine); i++) {
691 ret = nvkm_memory_new(device, NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST,
692 0x8000, 0x1000, false,
693 &fifo->engine[i].runlist[0]);
694 if (ret)
695 return ret;
696
697 ret = nvkm_memory_new(device, NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST,
698 0x8000, 0x1000, false,
699 &fifo->engine[i].runlist[1]);
700 if (ret)
701 return ret;
702
703#ifdef __NetBSD__
704 spin_lock_init(&fifo->engine[i].lock);
705 DRM_INIT_WAITQUEUE(&fifo->engine[i].wait, "gk104fifo");
706#else
707 init_waitqueue_head(&fifo->engine[i].wait);
708#endif
709 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&fifo->engine[i].chan);
710 }
711
712 ret = nvkm_memory_new(device, NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST,
713 fifo->base.nr * 0x200, 0x1000, true,
714 &fifo->user.mem);
715 if (ret)
716 return ret;
717
718 ret = nvkm_bar_umap(device->bar, fifo->base.nr * 0x200, 12,
719 &fifo->user.bar);
720 if (ret)
721 return ret;
722
723 nvkm_memory_map(fifo->user.mem, &fifo->user.bar, 0);
724 return 0;
725}
726
727void
728gk104_fifo_init(struct nvkm_fifo *base)
729{
730 struct gk104_fifo *fifo = gk104_fifo(base);
731 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
732 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
733 int i;
734
735 /* enable all available PBDMA units */
736 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x000204, 0xffffffff);
737 fifo->spoon_nr = hweight32(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x000204));
738 nvkm_debug(subdev, "%d PBDMA unit(s)\n", fifo->spoon_nr);
739
740 /* PBDMA[n] */
741 for (i = 0; i < fifo->spoon_nr; i++) {
742 nvkm_mask(device, 0x04013c + (i * 0x2000), 0x10000100, 0x00000000);
743 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x040108 + (i * 0x2000), 0xffffffff); /* INTR */
744 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x04010c + (i * 0x2000), 0xfffffeff); /* INTREN */
745 }
746
747 /* PBDMA[n].HCE */
748 for (i = 0; i < fifo->spoon_nr; i++) {
749 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x040148 + (i * 0x2000), 0xffffffff); /* INTR */
750 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x04014c + (i * 0x2000), 0xffffffff); /* INTREN */
751 }
752
753 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002254, 0x10000000 | fifo->user.bar.offset >> 12);
754
755 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002100, 0xffffffff);
756 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002140, 0x7fffffff);
757}
758
759void *
760gk104_fifo_dtor(struct nvkm_fifo *base)
761{
762 struct gk104_fifo *fifo = gk104_fifo(base);
763 int i;
764
765 nvkm_vm_put(&fifo->user.bar);
766 nvkm_memory_del(&fifo->user.mem);
767
768 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(fifo->engine); i++) {
769#ifdef __NetBSD__
770 DRM_DESTROY_WAITQUEUE(&fifo->engine[i].wait);
771 spin_lock_destroy(&fifo->engine[i].lock);
772#endif
773 nvkm_memory_del(&fifo->engine[i].runlist[1]);
774 nvkm_memory_del(&fifo->engine[i].runlist[0]);
775 }
776
777 return fifo;
778}
779
780int
781gk104_fifo_new_(const struct nvkm_fifo_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
782 int index, int nr, struct nvkm_fifo **pfifo)
783{
784 struct gk104_fifo *fifo;
785
786 if (!(fifo = kzalloc(sizeof(*fifo), GFP_KERNEL)))
787 return -ENOMEM;
788 INIT_WORK(&fifo->fault, gk104_fifo_recover_work);
789 *pfifo = &fifo->base;
790
791 return nvkm_fifo_ctor(func, device, index, nr, &fifo->base);
792}
793
794static const struct nvkm_fifo_func
795gk104_fifo = {
796 .dtor = gk104_fifo_dtor,
797 .oneinit = gk104_fifo_oneinit,
798 .init = gk104_fifo_init,
799 .fini = gk104_fifo_fini,
800 .intr = gk104_fifo_intr,
801 .uevent_init = gk104_fifo_uevent_init,
802 .uevent_fini = gk104_fifo_uevent_fini,
803 .chan = {
804 &gk104_fifo_gpfifo_oclass,
805 NULL
806 },
807};
808
809int
810gk104_fifo_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_fifo **pfifo)
811{
812 return gk104_fifo_new_(&gk104_fifo, device, index, 4096, pfifo);
813}
